</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3036512FFBCFFD9FF58FE284097E2CC" pageId="18" pageNumber="488" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA63699FFBCFFD9FF58FE284097E2CC" blockId="18.[134,781,160,1700]" pageId="18" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFBCFFD9FF58FE28401BE2AA" bold="true" box="[157,298,422,444]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="488">Etymology—</emphasis>
The epithet 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFBCFFD9FE6FFE28433DE2AD" box="[426,524,422,443]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="18" pageNumber="488" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lignescens">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFBCFFD9FE6FFE28433DE2AD" box="[426,524,422,443]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="488">lignescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the lignescent, woody habit of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
